title: Joe Kernan (politician)
added: In 2004, Kernan became the first governor of Indiana in 48 years to spare the life of an inmate on [[death row]], when, just days before his scheduled execution, Kernan commuted the sentence of Darnell Williams to life in prison without parole.<ref name="Davies2020"/>
